## IEmbeddable.getOutput() method

Output state is:

- State that should not change once the embeddable is instantiated, or - State that is derived from the input state, or - State that only the embeddable instance itself knows about, or the factory.

Examples: editUrl, title taken from a saved object, if your input state was first name and last name, your output state could be greeting.

<b>Signature:</b>

```typescript
getOutput(): Readonly<O>;
```
<b>Returns:</b>

`Readonly<O>`
